## Codebase discoveries (verified on this branch)
- weave.init("entity/project") configures the OTLP exporter to
  /agents/otel/v1/traces (weave_init.py::_setup_session_tracing, urls.py) AND
  registers the integration import hook. No project_id header (Python routes via
  Resource attrs wandb.entity/wandb.project). init defers if a real
  TracerProvider already exists.
- Native OTEL agent-span integrations: openai_agents, claude_agent_sdk,
  google_adk. Other integrations emit LEGACY calls, not agent spans. Plain openai
  is NOT auto-patched under use_otel_v2=True (default) -> treat as manual.
- Manual API = weave.session: start_session/start_turn/turn.llm/turn.tool/
  subagent (context managers) OR log_turn/log_session (batch).

## Hints for future agents
- OFFLINE VERIFY TECHNIQUE: set a global TracerProvider + InMemorySpanExporter
  BEFORE running; weave.session + the integration OTEL processors grab the global
  tracer at emit time -> spans captured with NO weave.init/network/creds.
  set_tracer_provider is once-per-process -> run each check in its own subprocess
  (examples/run_all.py does this).
- openai_agents native offline: a fake Model yields only Function+Agent spans
  (NO chat); to get chat spans, back the Agent with a real
  OpenAIChatCompletionsModel over httpx.MockTransport (examples/native_openai_agents/fake_backend.py).
  OpenAIAgentsOtelPatcher.attempt_patch() + set_trace_processors([proc]) to drop
  the SDK's default OpenAI uploader (avoids a 401).
- scripts/verify_instrumentation.py only works for the MANUAL path; the native
  processor only attaches via weave.init() (network). SKILL.md Step 4 documents this.

